On May 6, 2022, the President signed into law S. 400, the "William T. Coleman, Jr. and Norman Y. Mineta Department of Transportation Headquarters Act." This law designates the headquarters building of the Department of Transportation in Washington, DC as the William T. Coleman, Jr. and Norman Y. Mineta Federal Building. The article expresses gratitude to Senators Wicker, Cantwell, Carper, Capito, Tim Scott, Booker, Warnock, Inhofe, Duckworth, and others, as well as Representatives DeFazio and Carson, for their leadership in this matter.